HEADWORD: Wedge-shell
<hw>Wedge"-shell`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>Any one of numerous species of small marine bivalves belonging to
<gen>Donax</gen> and allied genera in which the shell is
wedge-shaped.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Wedge-tailed</ent>⟦br⟧
